From fbcadcb4b33af657d6befc1740ba854759ad4a71 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Ramesh Mandal <ramesh@6epixels.com>
Date: Fri, 3 Jul 2026 03:05:08 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] feat(m9): presence picker, PiP floating chat, presence
 masking, contact management

Server (20/20 tests):
- real presence statuses (online/away/busy/appear-offline) carried in
  hello + live 'presence' event, broadcast via roster
- per-viewer presence masking (presence_hide): roster is personalized
  per viewer; masked users appear offline to that viewer ONLY while
  messages continue to flow both ways (masking is not blocking)
- connection_remove: silent severance (no notification to the other
  side), messaging barred until a new consent request

Extension:
- avatar click in header -> presence menu (Online/Away/Busy/Appear
  offline) with live broadcast + honest microcopy
- Document Picture-in-Picture floating chat: always-on-top window that
  survives browser minimize; styles cloned; feature-detected; Settings
  kill-switch; opening PiP presents you Online, closing restores your
  chosen status
- contact management: add by @username (sends consent request), rename
  (local alias, never leaves the device, shown alongside real name),
  remove (silent server severance + local cleanup) - via Contacts row
  menu and the InfoPanel
- InfoPanel: per-contact 'Appear offline to @x' toggle with system
  notice clarifying messages still work
- roster presence flows into contacts; aliases survive roster refreshes
